One can precisely handle exceptions with JUnit's ExpectedException:<p><a href="http://kentbeck.github.com/junit/javadoc/4.10/org/junit/rules/ExpectedException.html" rel="nofollow">http://kentbeck.github.com/junit/javadoc/4.10/org/junit/rule...</a><p>This is more compact and declarative than the usual<p><pre><code>  try {
      ...;
      fail();
  } catch (...) {
      // expected
  }</code></pre>
